09/06/2006
ZAGREB, Croatia -- The Office for the Suppression of Corruption and Organised Crime (USKOK), working with Croatian and Slovenian police, announced the discovery of an illegal arms factory in Novi Golubovec, a town in northwestern Croatia near the border with Slovenia. USKOK chief Dinko Cvitan says the factory produced various types of high quality pistols, revolvers, automatic pistols and machine guns. Ten people have been arrested and more than 50 investigated in connection with the international arms smuggling ring. (Poslovni Dnevnik - 09/06/06; HINA - 08/06/06)
